maize-94: fs.h includes <stddef.h> for size_t.

Upstream file/function: fs.h (header).
Why: struct recursor has a size_t field but fs.h never includes a size_t provider,
relying on the includer having pulled one in first (upstream builds get it
transitively). Under Maize's -nostdinc RT slice, cp.c/rm.c include fs.h before any
stdio/stddef, so size_t is undefined at struct-parse time. Add the explicit
<stddef.h> include fs.h always needed.
diff --git a/fs.h b/fs.h
index 00ecd3b..eceb9e5 100644
--- a/fs.h
+++ b/fs.h
@@ -1,4 +1,5 @@
 /* See LICENSE file for copyright and license details. */
+#include <stddef.h>
 #include <limits.h>
 #include <sys/stat.h>
 #include <sys/types.h>
